docs/TEST_GATES.md:141:When changing the local cockpit, cockpit action registry, cockpit CLI adapter, `./ns cockpit` shortcuts, or `./ns-menu` cockpit entries, run unit tests plus explicit CLI smoke commands.
docs/TEST_GATES.md:157:The action registry must preserve explicit safety classification. Machine-readable inventory output must remain parseable JSON and must not execute actions. Read-only cockpit commands must not execute destructive Git, release, tag, merge, cleanup, or remote operations. `cockpit run` may execute registered `read_only` actions through argument-vector execution. Bounded actions may be listed as action metadata, but they must be blocked unless an explicit bounded-action allow path is used. Destructive actions must remain blocked.
docs/STATUS.md:31:PR #255 added an inspect-only cockpit action selection view. `agentic-kit cockpit select` renders a numbered action list from the central cockpit action registry without executing actions. `./ns select` delegates to that command, and `./ns-menu` exposes it as a numbered entry without adding new shell execution logic.
docs/STATUS.md:47:The cockpit action registry remains the central source of truth. `cockpit actions --json` exposes machine-readable metadata without executing actions. `cockpit select` exposes a human numbered selection view without executing actions. `cockpit run` remains the execution path and allows registered read-only actions by default. Bounded or destructive Git, release, tag, merge, cleanup, or remote operations remain blocked by default.
docs/STATUS.md:233:v0.3.23 control workflow consolidation is integrated on main. The release/PR/finalization workflow now has a shared deterministic control model with machine-readable target states, a stop-on-fail slice runner core, documented control-state semantics, a target-state-aware `./ns slice-runner`, early-stop release-gate behavior when release metadata is missing, and automated release metadata preparation in `./ns release-prep`. This addresses the recurring standard-error class where already reached target states, retryable pending states, or failed core patches caused misleading follow-up failures.
docs/STATUS.md:239:PR #320 added read-only `./ns pr-cleanup` classification for stale and relevant open PRs. The command classifies Dependabot PRs, active feature PRs, release-prep PRs, stale docs finalization PRs, superseded docs finalization PRs, conflicting relevant PRs, and safe-to-close PRs without mutating GitHub or Git state.
